<!-- @include callout { "kind": "risk", "title": "SSE may not stream progressively under workerd", "body": "toServerSentEventsResponse() behavior under the Workers runtime is inferred-not-documented. If the runtime flushes the whole response at once, the streaming architecture needs a shape-level rethink. Surface the failure immediately — do not work around it." } -->

<div class="callout callout-risk">
  <div class="callout-title">Risk (high): SSE may not stream progressively under workerd</div>
  <div class="callout-body">toServerSentEventsResponse() behavior under the Workers runtime is inferred-not-documented. If the runtime flushes the whole response at once, the streaming architecture needs a shape-level rethink. Surface the failure immediately — do not work around it silently.</div>
</div>

<div class="callout callout-warn">
  <div class="callout-title">Risk (medium): OpenRouter native adapter tool calling may still be broken</div>
  <div class="callout-body">Broke May 2026, reportedly fixed June. If broken at implement time, the OpenAI-adapter-baseURL fallback becomes the default — AC-PP3 (adapter-swap test) proves this swap is zero-callsite-change.</div>
</div>

<div class="callout callout-info">
  <div class="callout-title">Residual: live OpenRouter smoke requires API key</div>
  <div class="callout-body">AC-PP2b (live tool-call) is a pre-registered residual cleared by a tagged run with OPENROUTER_API_KEY present. Mocked proof (AC-PP2a) is the immediate automated evidence.</div>
</div>

